section.work-experience-list
  .section-title
    h3 Work
    
  .section-content
    
    .work-experince
      .work-header
        .work-duration
          p Jun/2017
          p Nov/2016
        .work-title
          p.title Business Analyst & Operations Manager
          p.company Comida da Gente
        .work-website
          a(href="http://www.comidadagente.org/") comidadagente.org
      .work-description
        p As a Business Analyst for
          a(href="")  Comida da Gente
          |, I’ve been taking care of operations as well as strategies for the company and the clients. Alongside with the CEO, we’ve been co-managing the operations team. I am responsible for tripling the company’s income since november. I developed new tools, from spreadsheet scripts to django applications to analyze our customers data and come up with new ideas.
          a(href="")  Comida da Gente
          |  is a initiative that regards collaborative shopping through a network of consumers and small and local producers. The clients are both shoppers and producers.
          
    .work-experince
      .work-header
        .work-duration
          p Nov/2016
          p Jun/2015
        .work-title
          p.title Product Designer
          p.company Comida da Gente
        .work-website
          a(href="http://www.comidadagente.org/") comidadagente.org
      .work-description
        p I started working for Comida da Gente as a part of my graduation project in Design, which was the design of an online platform that would comprehend the necessities of the initiative, focusing on user experience. The project itself was highly praised and got the maximum grade. From February to November I worked alone on all the tasks regarding the platform: field research, user research, interviews with stakeholder, information architecture, strategy, navigation, sketches, wireframes, user journey, heuristics, high-fidelity prototyping, usability tests... Starting November I was promoted to business analyst due to my extensive knowledge on the business.
        
    .work-experince
      .work-header
        .work-duration
          p Sep/2015
          p Jun/2015
        .work-title
          p.title Product Designer
          p.company Smart Living Challenge
      .work-description
        p The SLC is a initiative from the Swedish Institute held in 3 cities worldwide in 2015. The theme for Rio was mobility and it began with an open call for ideas and a selection of the participants based on those. Throughout 12 weeks we had several meetings and worked on designing a scalable and modular conceptual project that could be implemented in the Federal University main campus in Rio. By the end of the process we presented it at the Embassy of Sweden in Brasília to relevant authorities on the field. Also, the Swedish Institute presented it as a part of their main presentation at the Sustainable Innovation Forum in Paris (COP21).
        
    .work-experince
      .work-header
        .work-duration
          p Mai/2015
          p Mai/2014
        .work-title
          p.title Developer
          p.company Huge Inc
        .work-website
          a(href="http://www.hugeinc.com/") hugeinc.com
      .work-description
        p Huge is an agency focused on developing digital solutions capable of delivering good experiences and improving people’s quality  of life. As an intern I was part of a team that was in charge of prototyping the projects. I was a part of about 5 projects, including the 
          a(href="")  Galeão International Airport
          | , shopping center company
          a(href="")  Multiplan
          |  and pro-bono donation platform
          a(href="")  E-Solidario
          | .
    
    .work-experince
      .work-header
        .work-duration
          p Feb/2012
          p Dec/2012
        .work-title
          p.title Developer
          p.company ICE Interactive
      .work-description
        p ICE Interactive was a company incubated at COPPE-UFRJ that focused on the development of multi-touch interactive surfaces using computer vision and audio processing. I was in charge of developing the interface of one of the products. That included not only the graphics but also some of the data intelligence.


